# ===========================================
# MULTIMODALITY LABELING SYSTEM - MAIN
# ===========================================
# This is the main .env.example file for the entire project
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env
# 2. Copy frontend/.env.example to frontend/.env  
# 3. Fill in your actual Supabase credentials in both files
# 4. Update API URLs based on your deployment setup

# ===========================================
# PROJECT OVERVIEW
# ===========================================
# This project consists of:
# - Frontend: React TypeScript app (port 3000)
# - Backend: FastAPI Python app (port 8000)
# - Database: Supabase PostgreSQL with authentication

# ===========================================
# QUICK SETUP CHECKLIST
# ===========================================
# □ Create Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# □ Get your Supabase URL and keys from project settings
# □ Copy .env.example files to .env in both frontend/ and backend/
# □ Update environment variables with your actual values
# □ Install dependencies: npm install (frontend) & pip install -r requirements.txt (backend)
# □ Start both servers: npm start (frontend) & python main.py (backend)

# ===========================================
# REQUIRED SUPABASE SETUP
# ===========================================
# You need these values from your Supabase project:
# - Project URL: https://your-project.supabase.co
# - Anon key: Used by frontend for authentication  
# - Service role key: Used by backend for database operations
# - JWT secret: Used by backend to verify auth tokens

# ===========================================
# ENVIRONMENT-SPECIFIC URLS
# ===========================================
# Development:
# - Frontend: http://localhost:3000
# - Backend: http://localhost:8000
# - Database: Supabase cloud

# Production:
# - Frontend: https://your-app-domain.com
# - Backend: https://your-api-domain.com  
# - Database: Supabase cloud

# ===========================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ===========================================
# For production deployment:
# 1. Update REACT_APP_API_URL to your production backend URL
# 2. Update BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS to include your production frontend URL
# 3. Consider using environment-specific .env files (.env.prod, .env.staging)
# 4. Never commit actual .env files - only .env.example files should be in git

# ===========================================
# SECURITY REMINDERS
# ===========================================
# ⚠️  Add .env to .gitignore (should already be done)
# ⚠️  Never share service role keys publicly
# ⚠️  Rotate keys if they're accidentally exposed
# ⚠️  Use least-privilege access for database policies